CAMERON-IBERIA-JEFFERSON-ST. MARY-VERMILION-
457 PM CDT SAT SEP 13 2008

...TROPICAL STORM WARNING IS CANCELLED...

...NEW INFORMATION...

TROPICAL STORM WARNING ALONG THE TEXAS AND LOUISIANA
COASTLINES HAVE BEEN DISCONTINUED.

...AREAS AFFECTED...

THIS STATEMENT RECOMMENDS ACTIONS TO BE TAKEN BY PERSONS IN THE
FOLLOWING COUNTIES OR MARINE AREAS:

	CAMERON...IBERIA...JEFFERSON...ST. MARY...VERMILION.

...WATCHES/WARNINGS...

THE FOLLOWING WATCHES AND WARNINGS ARE CURRENTLY IN EFFECT FOR
THIS AREA:

	TORNADO WATCH.

...PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...

RESIDENTS ARE URGED TO STAY AWAY FROM FLOODED AREAS. CURFEWS ARE
IN EFFECT AT MANY LOCATIONS. PLEASE LISTEN TO RADIO OR TELEVISION
FOR FURTHER UPDATES.

...STORM SURGE AND STORM TIDE...

CURRENT STORM SURGE VALUES WERE ESTIMATED TO BE 7 TO 9 FEET BETWEEN
SABINE PASS AND CAMERON...AND 2 TO 6 FEET BETWEEN INTRACOASTAL
CITY AND CYPREMORT POINT. THESE VALUES ARE EXPECTED TO CONTINUE TO FALL
THROUGH SLOWLY THROUGH THIS EVENING.

...WINDS...

THROUGH THE LATE AFTERNOON INTO EARLY TONIGHT...WIND GUSTS WILL
VARY FROM 35 TO 45 MPH ACROSS JEFFERSON COUNTY AND CAMERON
PARISH...TO 30 TO 40 MPH ACROSS VERMILION...COASTAL IBERIA..AND
ST. MARY PARISHES. AFTER MIDNIGHT...WINDS GUSTS WILL CONTINUE TO
FALL INTO THE 20 TO 25 MPH RANGE.

...INLAND FLOODING...

INLAND LOCATIONS SUCH AS HACKBERRY...GRAND LAKE...AND FRANKLIN
WILL CONTINUE TO SEE INLAND FLOODING FOR THE REST OF THE AFTERNOON
INTO SUNDAY.

...TORNADOES...

A TORNADO WATCH IS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM.

...NEXT UPDATE...

THIS WILL BE THE LAST UPDATE ON THIS EVENT.

