ALLEN-BEAUREGARD-CALCASIEU-HARDIN-JASPER-JEFFERSON DAVIS-NEWTON-
ORANGE-TYLER-VERNON-
457 PM CDT SAT SEP 13 2008

...TROPICAL STORM WIND WARNING IS CANCELLED...

...NEW INFORMATION...

TROPICAL STORM IKE CONTINUES TO WEAKEN OVER NORTHEAST TEXAS.

...AREAS AFFECTED...

THIS STATEMENT RECOMMENDS ACTIONS TO BE TAKEN BY PERSONS IN THE
FOLLOWING COUNTIES OR MARINE AREAS:

	ALLEN...BEAUREGARD...CALCASIEU...HARDIN...JASPER...JEFFERSON 
	DAVIS...NEWTON...ORANGE...TYLER...VERNON.

...WATCHES/WARNINGS...

THE FOLLOWING WATCHES AND WARNINGS ARE CURRENTLY IN EFFECT FOR
THIS AREA:

	TORNADO WATCH.
 
...PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...

STAY INDOORS AND STAY SAFE. DO NOT INHIBIT RESCUE PERSONNEL WHILE
THEY ARE WORKING FOR THE REST OF THIS AFTERNOON INTO TONIGHT. SERVICE
WORKERS WILL BE HARD AT WORK RESTORING POWER AND OTHER SERVICES.

...WINDS...

SOUTHERLY WINDS GUST OF 30 TO 40 MPH CAN BE EXPECTED FOR THE REST
OF THE THIS AFTERNOON. GUSTY WINDS WILL BE ON THE DECREASE
TONIGHT WITH WIND GUST DROPPING DOWN INTO THE 15 TO 25 MPH
RANGE.

...INLAND FLOODING...

STORM SURGE FROM THE COAST WILL CONTINUE TO CAUSE SIGNIFICANT
FLOOD PROBLEMS IN ORANGE COUNTY...INCLUDING THE BRIDGE CITY AND
DOWNTOWN ORANGE AREAS. IN CALCASIEU PARISH...PARTS OF SULPHUR...
WESTLAKE...AND LAKE CHARLES WILL CONTINUE TO SEE FLOOD WATERS.

...TORNADOES...

A TORNADO WATCH IS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM.

...NEXT UPDATE...

THIS WILL BE THE LAST UPDATE ON THIS EVENT.

